            <thetext>In a more recent version of ImageMagick, 6.5.4.-8, passing input files with the 
&#39;@&#39; sigil only works for plain file names, with now path components. This makes 
the generator break when combining images, as the input image paths are placed 
into a temporary file, which is  passed with absolute path name to the 
&#39;montage&#39; command, e.g. &#39;montage .... @/tmp/tempiXWXS2 &lt;output-file&gt;&#39;.

The error message is:
montage: unable to open image `@/tmp/tempiXWXS2&#39;: No such file or directory @ 
blob.c/OpenBlob/2480.

This used to work with e.g. the 6.3.x line of ImageMagick.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
